               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-67r: Sword of Divinity, Säyfä Mäläkot, ሠይፈ፡ መለኮት፡, AbbCat 171, <locus target="#29v"/>, Notice 104; AbbCat 186, <locus target="#104"/>, Notice 233; StrLin 47, f.88v;  EMML 1169, <locus target="#120b"/>, EMIP 33:10. Arranged for the days of the week: F<locus target="#1r"/>-14a: Introduction.  Monday (<locus target="#14r"/>), Tuesday (<locus target="#23r"/>), Wednesday (<locus target="#31v"/>), Thursday (<locus target="#37v"/>), Friday (<locus target="#46r"/>), Saturday (<locus target="#55v"/>), Sunday (<locus target="#61r"/>). Each day ends with a miracle of the Trinity: Monday (21v), Tuesday (<locus target="#30v"/>), Wednesday (<locus target="#36v"/>),  Thursday (<locus target="#45r"/>), Friday (<locus target="#54v"/>), Saturay (<locus target="#59v"/>), Sunday (<locus target="#65v"/>). F<locus target="#67v"/>-78r: Image of the Trinity, Mälk‘a Śǝllase, መልክአ፡ ሥላሴ፡. Répertoire 20; MG 189ff. Incipit : ሰላም፡ ለህላዌክሙ፡ ዘይመውዕ፡ ህላውያተ፡. F<locus target="#5v"/> and passim, mention the owners, ብርሃነ ትንሣኤ ጽጌ, and his wife, ወለተ ሰንበት. <locus target="#67r"/> mentions the scribe ሣህ[ለ] ጊዮርጊስ.</summary>
